Step01:

🔧 Steps:
	1. Create an OpenAI account: https://platform.openai.com
	2. Get API Key.(https://platform.openai.com/api-keys)
Step-by-Step: How to Get Your OpenAI API Key
	1. Go to OpenAI’s Platform
👉 https://platform.openai.com/
	2. Sign in / Sign up
		○ Use your Google account or email to create an OpenAI account if you don’t have one.
	3. Go to API Keys Section
		○ Once logged in, visit:
👉 https://platform.openai.com/account/api-keys
	4. Click “Create new secret key”
		○ A new key will be generated.
		○ Copy it immediately — you won’t be able to see it again.

# Install SDK

import openai

openai.api_key = "your-api-key"

response = openai.ChatCompletion.create(
    model="gpt-4",
    messages=[
        {"role": "system", "content": "You are a travel guide"},
        {"role": "user", "content": "Plan me a 3-day trip to Goa"}
    ]
)

print(response["choices"][0]["message"]["content"])

##Option 2: Fine-Tune GPT-3.5 or Smaller Models with OpenAI
	You can upload your data to fine-tune GPT-3.5 for better control.
🔧 Steps:
	1. Prepare your dataset (JSONL format).
	2. Use OpenAI CLI to upload and fine-tune.


import streamlit as st
import openai
from dotenv import load_dotenv
import os

load_dotenv()
openai.api_key = os.getenv("OPENAI_API_KEY")

st.set_page_config(page_title="My GPT Chatbot", layout="centered")
st.title("🤖 Custom ChatGPT Assistant")

if "messages" not in st.session_state:
    st.session_state.messages = []

for msg in st.session_state.messages:
    st.chat_message(msg["role"]).write(msg["content"])

user_input = st.chat_input("Say something...")

if user_input:
    st.session_state.messages.append({"role": "user", "content": user_input})
    st.chat_message("user").write(user_input)

    response = openai.ChatCompletion.create(
        model="gpt-4",  # or "gpt-3.5-turbo"
        messages=st.session_state.messages
    )

    reply = response["choices"][0]["message"]["content"]
    st.session_state.messages.append({"role": "assistant", "content": reply})
    st.chat_message("assistant").write(reply)


Final and Run command : 
"streamlit run chatbot.py"

